column5: Fishing was tough today.. change in weather today made for mostly small stuff... and my poor daughter couldn't catch a fish..... till about 1/2 an hour before dark... then she got this on a topwater.. about 15 feet from the boat...came right outta the water when it smashed it... scared the crap outta me.. lol  Gotta a great release vid.. ill post when i got better bandwidth!
Way to go Jaden......Dad was always a better camera man than fisherman
NICE!!!  Beet ya that ones on Facebook!
big, chunky pike  very cool how the finger nails match the sweater too (Hahaha)  I really liked the Matachewan area and the vibe when I have been there
Way to go Jaden. I'm looking forward to seeing the video.
That's a GREAT pike! Congrat's to Jaden.
Top water? Wow, that would scare me too!
Thats an amazing fish!!! great going
excellent job o and by the way T.J. was once again out fished by the female population at J.J.   Art
